race.description: Dearaugo And Lea Electrical Maiden Plate
race.comment: PONTE ARCOBALENO (8) is another knocking on the door, just finding one better at all three runs this time in. He found the line well at Swan Hill last time and the extra 100m should be suitable for the son of Castelvecchio. TANANA (13) resumed with a sound run at Ballarat when third, albeit beaten seven lengths by an impressive winner, who has since won again in town. That form should hold up and she'll strip fitter with improvement to come. BLACKHILL BOY (3) has been solid in two runs to date and will be better for them with a soft run from the inside. AL PRANCER (2) resumes and can be strong late.
